Czech Party Wants Posts, Threatens to Quit Cabinet, Pravo Says

-- B y   A n d r e a   D u d i k
-- 
2011-06-04T07:27:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/czech-party-wants-posts-threatens-to-quit-cabinet-pravo-says.html
The smallest Czech coalition party
threatened to quit the Cabinet next week if it doesn’t get four
ministry posts,  Pravo  daily reported, citing Public Affairs
negotiator Vit Barta.  Barta, a former transportation minister, said Prime
Minister Petr Necas has until June 7 to meet the party’s
demands, according to the newspaper. Representatives of the
three-party ruling coalition will meet tomorrow to discuss the
situation, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Dudik in Prague at 
 adudikova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  